summary: tony had never had friends. he had acquaintances, kids who were near his own age and ran in the same circles (rich and gleaming...
body:
tony had never had friends. he had acquaintances, kids who were near his own age and ran in the same circles (rich and gleaming and distant), kids who would gather round during their parents’ parties and try to waste the time away; but he never had friends.

(the closest he’d ever come was janet, sharp as a tack and brilliant, all gleaming diamond and unapologetic brashness.)

then he gets to mit, ready for more false niceties with kids who dont actually like him but dont despise him, and thats not what he gets. (well, it is, but not fully, not like it had always been before.)

because james rhodes is genuine and vibrant, an antithesis to what tony was brought up on (closed doors and muted colors and false smiles). he’s only two years older than tony, (nearly smarter than him, too) and when they shake hands, and james uses it to pull him into a hug, something in tony clings to james, even after they’ve pulled apart.

(and tony knows that some bright piece of his heart is still sewn over rhodey’s own, the stitches tight and true.)

summary: #12 (CANDLES)  The towering sorcerer with silver-streaked hair remained stoic through the initial flurry of panic after...
body:
#12 (CANDLES) 

The towering sorcerer with silver-streaked hair remained stoic through the initial flurry of panic after returning from Titan. He said nothing while Cap and Banner and Rhodes and so many other stood at the podium to speak. His eyes hadn’t shifted from long walnut casket while Pepper Potts tearfully placed a bundle of lilies on the glossy lid.  

And though many guessed, none knew. Not for sure, at least. Peter Parker had been with the pair, but the boy remained mum about the ordeal. All anyone really knew was that two candles sat on either side of Tony Stark’s fresh grave, and, as if by magic, their flames always shone brightly.

@rfinnegan (I’m not sure if you were talking to me or not but here’s a thing anyway)

answer:
#46 (SHIMMER) 

Tony wondered if it was magic. If there was some sort of spell involved. It must be. It had to be. First, they glistened like drops of quartz. Then they were as hypnotically indigo as the sea. Now they twinkle not too unlike the emerald stone that hung from the long neck below. Yes, Stephen Strange must use some spell on his eyes, and it seemed Tony Stark was the only one looking close enough to notice.

summary: #1 (DON’T LEAVE) & #46 (SHIMMER)   The stillness was frightening; the silence deadly. It reminded him of Titan. Of gentle...
body:
#1 (DON’T LEAVE) & #46 (SHIMMER) 

 The stillness was frightening; the silence deadly. It reminded him of Titan. Of gentle breezes. Of ash.

The only movement in the room was the shimmer of reflected light, tinged amber by the whiskey in Tony’s crystal glass, dancing across the carpeted floor in time with the violent quivering of his fingers. Though his drunken haze, Tony thought he saw the once familiar swish of scarlet fabric whipping around the corner and hope grabbed his aching heart with a vice grip. “Don’t leave,” Tony begged weakly, stumbling forward, hand reaching out to close around empty air. “Please don’t leave me alone again.”

@taurusart

Ulfr: Please, what I’ve seen makes your suits look like tinfoil costumes.

Tony: Didn’t seem the case when I was blasting your frosty, giant, ass out the sky.

Ulfr [smiles]: I love being hit on me, Stark, but how about we finish this first?

Tony: …Wow…

I don’t know…God help me, I just don’t know, LMAO!! I just…I found the Lee gif in my hunts and it built from there. That said, I so wanna have Ulfr and Tony meet in the future now. 😅

Y'all are wearing that in Spider-Man far from home, Peter is going to be suffering PTSD and morning Tony who probably sacrificed himself so he and many others could live. But honestly, it’s much more likely that however Peter comes back, he won’t remember all the events that saved him or what happened before. It would work much better to retcon continuity for the future, if Peter didn’t remember Tony at all.

Prepare to suffer.
